  "html": "<h1>Applies to</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>PCI DSS Requirement 8.2</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1>What to Check For</h1>\n  <p>Users should be authenticated before gaining access to the system(s).</p>\n  <h1>Why</h1>\n  <p>Authenticating the users enables access control.</p>\n  <h1>How to Check</h1>\n  <p>Observe the users accessing the system to make sure they have to log in before having access granted.</p>\n  <h1>How to Fix</h1>\n  <p>Most modern Operating Systems implement user authentication. Use a directory service, such as Microsoft Active Directory, to set up centralized authentication and user management in an enterprise environment. Setting up Active Directory is a common IT skill,\n and your company should have at least one person that has it. The actual process involves many steps and varies by environment.&amp;nbsp;Install and configure a domain controller. Join all the workstations to the domain. Create user accounts on the domain controller\n for each authorized user. Configure the access control system. Use the domain controller for authentication in your custom applications.</p>"
